Class
Description
AlertHandler
The AlertHandler class is a singleton class that manages the display of alert messages in a JavaFX application.
BloodPressure
Enumeration representing different levels of blood pressure.
DB_Model
DB_Model - Class that performs all database operations - Singleton Design Pattern
Drug
Represents a drug in the system.
DrugIntake
This class represents a drug intake that a patient takes for a specific therapy.
Log
This class represents a log containing information related to a medical operation or procedure, such as a medication administration.
loginController
The controller class for the login view
Main
The Main class is the entry point of the application.
Measurement
The Measurement class represents a single measurement of blood pressure taken from a patient.
MeasurementPathology
This class represents a measurement-pathology association, linking a measurement to a pathology.
MeasurementSymptom
Represents a relationship between a measurement and a symptom.
MeasurementTherapy
Represents a measurement associated with a therapy in a medical record.
Pathology
A class representing a pathology, identified by an integer ID and a description.
Patient
The Patient class represents a single patient and extend the cass User.
PatientPathology
The PatientPathology class represents a pathology that a patient can have.
patientViewController
The controller class for the Patient view
Physician
A class representing a physician, which is a type of User.
physicianViewController
The controller class for the Patient view
showPatientViewController
The controller class for the show Patient view
stageController
This class is used to control the main stage of the application.
Symptom
Represents a symptom that a patient may experience.
Therapy
The Therapy class represents a therapy associated with a patient.
TherapyNotTaken
The TherapyNotTaken class represents a therapy that has not been taken by a patient.
User
The abstract User class represents a basic user in a system.
